Package: pawnr
Title: Computation of PAWN Sensitivity Indices
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Arnald",
           family = "Puy",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "arnald.puy@gmail.com")
Description: It computes PAWN sensitivity indices following 
    the approach described in Pianosi and Wagener 2015 <10.1016/j.envsoft.2015.01.004> and 
    Pianosi and Wagener 2018 <10.1016/j.envsoft.2018.07.019>. The 'pawnr' package also implements
    the algorithm by Khorashadi Zadeh et al. 2017 <doi:10.1016/j.envsoft.2017.02.001 > to 
    calculate the approximation error in the computation of PAWN indices, an approach 
    that allows to robustly screen influential from non-influential model inputs. Finally, it 
    also provides functions to obtain publication-quality figures of the model output 
    uncertainty and sensitivity-related analysis.
